Naming Conventions :

Classes and Interfaces :
First letter should be capital Camel case

Methods :
First letter lowercase camel case

Variables :
Should not start with underscore(‘_’) or dollar sign ‘$’ characters.
Single character variable names should be avoided

Constant variables :
Should be all uppercase with words separated by underscores (“_”).
public static final float POSITIVE_INFINITY = 1.0f / 0.0f;

Packages :
All-lowercase : com.assignmentnamingconventions

Enumeration :
names should be all uppercase letters.

Example :

class StringBuilderExample{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        StringBuilder stringBuilder=new StringBuilder("Hello, ");
        stringBuilder.append("Alina");
        System.out.println(sb);
    }
}